2. `L`/`itsL`: mostly lowercased `l` on the atom, but still uppercase `LMax`.
3. Some `std::vector<double>` left in MnD internal — save for a full MnD review+refactor

## qcLattice_3D
**Pinned design reviews**
- Scalars leaking through abstract interfaces: `ExternalG0Energy` (PW-specific, no molecular-ECP analogue)
  and the `double& Eh` out-param on `Repulsion(const FourierMap&, double&)`.
- `BasisSet<dcmplx>::Create{CD,Vxc}FitBasisSet` NA-stubs (`src/BasisSet/Imp/BasisSet.C`) — the "dirty code
  smell" to revisit ("PW reuses its own basis for fitting" ≠ "those fakes are fine").
- BZ-symmetry reduction — multi-k computes all k-points explicitly; fold to the irreducible wedge (+weights) using the crystal point group when k-counts grow. (Perf, not correctness.) see **Space-group support** in qcSymmetry
- DIIS appears numerical unstable: PlaneWaveDFT.FrameworkNaFThroughSCFIterator @ UnitTests/PlaneWaveDFTUT.C:1147
